-Variables: Loosely tight
----------
At runtime, by seeing value JS intelligently identify datatype
Until ES5 --> var for stroing values (var has disadvantages)
After ES6 --> Introduced let and Const along with var (Note: var and let are almost same)

let a = 4;
console.log(a);
console.log(typeof(a));
//null and undefined --> don't assign any value to a variable, it will be undefined

let b = 234.6;
console.log(typeof(b));

//let c = a + b;
//console.log(c);

var c = a + b;  //replaced with var to make it global
console.log(c)

-Note: We can not redeclare with let keyword, but possible with var keyword

//Reassigning a value to a variable
let c = "Rohit";
    c = a + b;   //Allowed in case of let
var c = "Rohit"; //Allowed in case of var

Note: For const, we can't reassign also, it will throw TypeError: Assignment to constant variable

